---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Quest Labs — Foundations">

<div class="page">

  <!-- COVER -->
  <div class="cover">
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Quest Labs · 2026</div>
    <div class="cover-title">Foundations.</div>
    <div class="cover-sub">Where this comes from, what holds it together, and what makes it distinctly Quest Labs.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="cta-group" style="justify-content:center; margin-bottom:2rem;">
    <a href="https://lu.ma/questlabs" class="cta-primary">Find a Sandbox Session →</a>
    <a href="/program" class="cta-secondary">Explore FLIP →</a>
  </div>

  <!-- 01 LINEAGE -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">01</div>
      <div class="section-title">Lineage</div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">These are some of the thinkers and frameworks that shaped what Quest Labs builds. Each one has a direct line to a specific product, method, or practice.</p>

    <div class="positionality-grid">

      <div class="pos-item pos-miller">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--teal)">Futures literacy as human capability</div>
        <div class="pos-year">Riel Miller · UNESCO Futures Literacy Programme</div>
        <div class="pos-what">Futures literacy as something people develop, not a prediction skill. The Futures Literacy Laboratory as a living research environment. "Rigorous imagining." This thread runs through every sandbox session and every gathering Quest Labs hosts.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="pos-item pos-inayat">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--gold)">Causal Layered Analysis</div>
        <div class="pos-year">Sohail Inayatullah · MetafutureSchool / UNESCO Chair</div>
        <div class="pos-what">CLA. Futures Triangle. Narrative Foresight. Portal of Possibilities grew out of conversation with this work. CLA MadLibs applies Inayatullah's four layers directly and makes academic rigor playful.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="pos-item pos-dunagan">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--violet)">Experiential futures</div>
        <div class="pos-year">Jake Dunagan · IFTF</div>
        <div class="pos-what">"Better surprised by a simulation than blindsided by reality." The Experiential Futures Ladder and serious games tradition is the spine of every interactive tool Quest Labs makes: Quest Cards, Black Menagerie, STEEPS Bingo.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="pos-item pos-candy">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--rose)">Postnormal Times</div>
        <div class="pos-year">Ziauddin Sardar</div>
        <div class="pos-what">Sardar's framework for navigating contradiction, complexity, and chaos is the theoretical heart of the Black Menagerie card game. The five archetypes are postnormal futures made playable.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="pos-item pos-milojevic" style="grid-column: span 2;">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--ember)">Sarkar Sandbox</div>
        <div class="pos-year">Modified from the Sarkar Game</div>
        <div class="pos-what">The sandbox session format at Quest Labs is a direct modification of the Sarkar Game, adapted for futures literacy education, participatory practice, and community inquiry.</div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 02 THE FRAMEWORK -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">02</div>
      <div class="section-title">The framework</div>
    </div>
    <div class="lore-grid">
      <div class="lore-text">
        <h2 class="section-title">Seven Literacies for a World in Transition</h2>
        <p>Our relationship to our futures has been <strong>crafted and commandeered</strong>. Decades of deficit-model education trained whole generations to react to crises rather than be the authors of alternative futures and to dance with uncertainty instead of trying to control the unprecedented.</p>
        <p>Quest Labs builds the <strong>infrastructure for what comes next</strong> while crumbling systems meet their maker. Built from scratch, from the ground up, with community wisdom as the foundation.</p>
        <p>The <strong>ABCDEFG Futures Literacies Framework</strong> emerged from <strong>545 contributions by 170 educators</strong> across two healing-centered gatherings. It is not a curriculum. It is a living methodology: seven interlocking capacities that, together, form a complete ecology of futures intelligence.</p>
        <p>This is shadow work and emergence work. <em>Everything everywhere all at once.</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="lore-visual">
        <div class="abcdefg-radial" id="radialChart"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 03 THE PRACTICE -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">03</div>
      <div class="section-title">The practice</div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">The framework emerged from lived experiences, not just theory behind a desk.</p>
    <p>Most learning prepares you for a world that already existed. Participatory Action Learning and Action Research (PALAR) prepares you for what is arriving. You learn by moving, by reflecting, by moving again, with a cohort of people navigating the same uncertainty from different angles. The moment you are trying to meet becomes the curriculum. We learn what we need to learn by doing what needs to be done, together, and paying attention. That is the whole methodology.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 04 DISTINCTLY QUEST LABS -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">04</div>
      <div class="section-title">What makes it distinctly Quest Labs</div>
    </div>

    <ul class="uvp-list">
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">1</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">Built from the braid</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">Multiple homes. Multiple epistemologies. Dena'ina land to Stanford to Berlin: not a straight line, but a braid. The positionality is the methodology. Everything Quest Labs builds holds more than one way of knowing at once: not as compromise, as design.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">2</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">The tools are the research are the toys</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">Every interactive tool, Quest Cards, Black Menagerie, STEEPS Bingo, CLA Mad Libs, is experiential futures methodology made operational. The experience is the gift. The play is the point.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">3</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">A living collective across four countries</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">The Founding Questors span Germany, South Africa, Canada, and the USA. Multiple disciplines. Already in motion.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- CLOSING -->
  <div class="sci-closing">
    <h2 class="sci-closing-heading">The methodology is living. Come meet it.</h2>
    <p class="sci-closing-body">The ABCDEFG framework, the tools, the lineage: these are not artifacts. They are practices in motion inside every FLIP cohort and every Sandbox Session.</p>
    <div class="sci-closing-links">
      <a href="/program#waitlist" class="btn-primary">Join the FLIP waitlist →</a>
      <a href="https://luma.com/questlabs" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Find a Sandbox Session →</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-bridge" style="max-width:860px; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto; padding-left:2.5rem; padding-right:2.5rem;">
    <p>The methodology is living. Come meet it.</p>
    <a href="https://lu.ma/questlabs" class="bridge-link">Find a Sandbox Session →</a>
    <a href="/educators" class="bridge-link" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Educator? Flip the Script is where this comes alive in the classroom →</a>
    <a href="/about#work-with-us" class="bridge-link" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Researcher or funder? Let's talk →</a>
  </div>

</div><!-- end .page -->

<script is:inline>
// ===== ABCDEFG RADIAL =====
const radial = document.getElementById('radialChart');
const letters = [
  { l: 'A', w: 'Affective', color: '#e8621a', angle: -90 },
  { l: 'B', w: 'Behavioral', color: '#d4a017', angle: -38 },
  { l: 'C', w: 'Cognitive', color: '#0fb8a0', angle: 14 },
  { l: 'D', w: 'Dialectical', color: '#c4446c', angle: 66 },
  { l: 'E', w: 'Experiential', color: '#7c3aed', angle: 118 },
  { l: 'F', w: 'Fun/Creative', color: '#0fb8a0', angle: 170 },
  { l: 'G', w: 'Generative', color: '#d4a017', angle: 222 }
];
const radius = 177;
letters.forEach(item => {
  const rad = (item.angle * Math.PI) / 180;
  const x = 240 + radius * Math.cos(rad);
  const y = 240 + radius * Math.sin(rad);
  const line = document.createElement('div');
  line.className = 'radial-line';
  const dist = radius - 60;
  line.style.cssText = `width:${dist}px; transform-origin: left center; transform: rotate(${item.angle}deg); left: 240px; top: 240px; background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(${hexToRgb(item.color)},0.3) 0%, transparent 100%);`;
  radial.appendChild(line);
  const node = document.createElement('div');
  node.className = 'radial-node';
  node.style.cssText = `left: ${x}px; top: ${y}px; border-color: ${item.color}40; --node-transform: translate(-50%,-50%); transform: translate(-50%,-50%);`;
  node.innerHTML = `<span class="nl" style="color:${item.color}">${item.l}</span><span class="nw">${item.w}</span>`;
  node.title = item.w;
  radial.appendChild(node);
});
const center = document.createElement('div');
center.className = 'radial-center';
center.textContent = 'Futures Literacies';
radial.appendChild(center);
function hexToRgb(hex) {
  const r = parseInt(hex.slice(1,3),16), g = parseInt(hex.slice(3,5),16), b = parseInt(hex.slice(5,7),16);
  return `${r},${g},${b}`;
}
</script>

<style>
  /* Science page: stack lore-grid and center the radial chart */
  .lore-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
  }
  .lore-visual {
    justify-content: center;
    height: auto !important;
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }
</style>

</Layout>
